const BUSINESS_INSIGHTS: Record<string, string> = {
  'injection-molding-defects': `The financial exposure from injection molding defects compounds with volume. ${PROBLEM_DATA['injection-molding-defects'].cost1}. ${PROBLEM_DATA['injection-molding-defects'].cost2}. For a high-volume program producing 500,000 parts monthly at 10% defect rate, the monthly production cost of defects — resin, press time, labor, overhead — exceeds $75,000. The downstream escape cost, if defects reach assembly or the field, is an order of magnitude higher.`,
  'tooling-failures': `Tooling failure is a production cost problem presented as a maintenance event. ${PROBLEM_DATA['tooling-failures'].cost1}. ${PROBLEM_DATA['tooling-failures'].cost2}. A production program generating $180,000 per month in output and experiencing one unplanned mold failure annually absorbs $360,000–$1.08M in production revenue impact — from a tooling specification shortcut that saved $20,000–$30,000 at program approval.`,
  'production-bottlenecks': `Throughput loss in injection molding is recoverable without capital investment. ${PROBLEM_DATA['production-bottlenecks'].cost1}. ${PROBLEM_DATA['production-bottlenecks'].cost2}. A 10-press operation recovering 20% cycle efficiency has effectively added 2 presses of capacity to its existing asset base — without equipment purchase, facility expansion, or headcount addition. The cycle time audit is the diagnostic that quantifies the opportunity before the capital meeting is scheduled.`,
  'scrap-rework-cost': `Scrap cost in injection molding is a process investment decision. ${PROBLEM_DATA['scrap-rework-cost'].cost1}. ${PROBLEM_DATA['scrap-rework-cost'].cost2}. Moving from 15% to 3% scrap on a $400,000 monthly resin program recovers $48,000 per month in production cost — $576,000 annually — from process documentation and SPC implementation that costs a fraction of one year's savings. The ROI is explicit and fast.`,
  'mold-downtime': `Mold downtime is a budgetable, predictable cost — when the PM program exists. ${PROBLEM_DATA['mold-downtime'].cost1}. ${PROBLEM_DATA['mold-downtime'].cost2}. A 15-mold operation implementing shot-count-based PM reduces unplanned downtime by 60–80% — converting $108,000 in monthly throughput loss from reactive failures into a fraction of that cost in planned, scheduled maintenance events.`,
  'poor-part-consistency': `Part consistency is a supply chain cost when the supplier's process is unstable. ${PROBLEM_DATA['poor-part-consistency'].cost1}. ${PROBLEM_DATA['poor-part-consistency'].cost2}. For a Tier 1 supplier absorbing a 30% assembly stoppage rate premium from an inconsistent injection-molded component, the labor and overhead cost per additional stoppage event accumulates faster than any incoming inspection program can address it. The fix is upstream — at the molding press, not at the receiving dock.`,
  'scaling-inefficiencies': `Scale-up failure in injection molding has a predictable cost profile. ${PROBLEM_DATA['scaling-inefficiencies'].cost1}. ${PROBLEM_DATA['scaling-inefficiencies'].cost2}. The 8-week tooling rebuild lead time triggered by a scale-up failure creates customer delivery gaps that carry their own cost — expediting, premium freight, contractual penalties, and customer relationship exposure that exceeds the direct engineering change cost by a multiple.`,
  'material-waste': `Material efficiency is a tooling cost decision with a multi-year financial tail. ${PROBLEM_DATA['material-waste'].cost1}. ${PROBLEM_DATA['material-waste'].cost2}. On a $1.2M annual resin program, moving from 18% to 5% material waste through hot runner tooling and purge optimization saves $156,000 annually. The tooling investment required to achieve this recovers in year one — and runs a positive return for every subsequent year of the program.`,
  'process-cost-leakage': `Process cost leakage is the most consistently underreported cost category in injection molding operations. ${PROBLEM_DATA['process-cost-leakage'].cost1}. ${PROBLEM_DATA['process-cost-leakage'].cost2}. A 10-press injection molding operation implementing SPC and recovering 60% of its process leakage captures $1.26M in annual cost improvement — from a monitoring system that costs less than 2% of that figure to implement and operate.`,
  'tooling-lifecycle-cost': `Tooling lifecycle cost is a program cost multiplier that most procurement decisions underweight. ${PROBLEM_DATA['tooling-lifecycle-cost'].cost1}. ${PROBLEM_DATA['tooling-lifecycle-cost'].cost2}. A tooling portfolio of 20 active molds with an average build cost of $55,000 carries an expected 5-year lifecycle cost of $220,000–$440,000 per mold — $4.4M–$8.8M across the portfolio. Programs that modeled this at tooling approval selected specifications that reduced the lifecycle multiple. Programs that did not are paying the difference in repair, downtime, and scrap.`,
}

